Applications for standard licences
	After section 24 of the 1974 Act insert—
	“24AApplications for standard licences
		An application for a standard licence shall, in relation to each type ofbusiness which is covered by the application, state whether the applicant isapplying—
			for the licence to cover the carrying on of that type of business with nolimitation; or
			for the licence to cover the carrying on of that type of business only sofar as it falls within one or more descriptions of business.
		An application within subsection (1)(b) in relation to a type of businessshall set out the description or descriptions of business in question.
		References in this Part to a type of business are references to a type ofbusiness within subsection (4).
		The types of business within this subsection are—
			a consumer credit business;
			a consumer hire business;
			a business so far as it comprises or relates to credit brokerage;
			a business so far as it comprises or relates to debt-adjusting;
			a business so far as it comprises or relates to debt-counselling;
			a business so far as it comprises or relates to debt-collecting;
			a business so far as it comprises or relates to debt administration;
			a business so far as it comprises or relates to the provision of creditinformation services;
			a business so far as it comprises or relates to the operation of a creditreference agency.
		The OFT—
			shall by general notice specify the descriptions of business which can beset out in an application for the purposes of subsection (2) in relation to atype of business;
			may by general notice provide that applications within subsection (1)(b)cannot be made in relation to one or more of the types of business withinsubsection (4)(c) to (i).
		The power of the OFT under subsection (5) includes power to make differentprovision for different cases or classes of case.”
